---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site.js';
const co = 'Sri Sahasrara Yogishwara Swami Mahapeetham';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy policy for Sri Sahasrara Yogishwara Swami Mahapeetham (sriyogi.site).">
  <PageHeader eyebrow="Legal" title="Privacy Policy" />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <p class="muted">Updated at 2023-03-01</p>

      <p>{co} (“we,” “our,” or “us”) is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how your personal information is collected, used, and disclosed by {co}.</p>
      <p>This Privacy Policy applies to our website and its associated subdomains (collectively, our “Service”). By accessing or using our Service, you signify that you have read, understood, and agree to our collection, storage, use, and disclosure of your personal information as described in this Privacy Policy and our Terms of Service.</p>

      <h2>Definitions and Key Terms</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cookie:</strong> small amount of data generated by a website and saved by your web browser. It is used to identify your browser, provide analytics, and remember information about you such as your language preference or login information.</li>
        <li><strong>Company:</strong> refers to {co} (#148, Omshree Plaza, DVG Road, Basavanagudi, Bengaluru 560004), responsible for your information under this Privacy Policy.</li>
        <li><strong>Country:</strong> where {co} or its owners/founders are based — in this case, India.</li>
        <li><strong>Customer:</strong> the company, organization or person that signs up to use the Service to manage relationships with consumers or service users.</li>
        <li><strong>Device:</strong> any internet-connected device such as a phone, tablet, or computer used to visit and use the services.</li>
        <li><strong>IP address:</strong> a number assigned to every device connected to the Internet, often used to identify the location from which a device connects.</li>
        <li><strong>Personnel:</strong> individuals employed by {co} or under contract to perform a service on its behalf.</li>
        <li><strong>Personal Data:</strong> any information that allows for the identification of a natural person.</li>
        <li><strong>Service:</strong> the service provided by {co} as described on this platform.</li>
        <li><strong>Third-party service:</strong> advertisers, contest sponsors, promotional and marketing partners, and others who provide content or whose products may interest you.</li>
        <li><strong>Website:</strong> {co}’s site, accessible at <a href="https://www.sriyogi.site">https://www.sriyogi.site</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>You:</strong> a person or entity registered with {co} to use the Services.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What Information Do We Collect?</h2>
      <p>We collect information from you when you visit our website, register on our site, place an order, subscribe to our newsletter, respond to a survey or fill out a form:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Name / Username</li>
        <li>Phone Numbers</li>
        <li>Email Addresses</li>
        <li>Mailing Addresses</li>
        <li>Billing Addresses</li>
        <li>Debit/credit card numbers</li>
        <li>Age</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How Do We Use The Information We Collect?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To personalize your experience and better respond to your individual needs</li>
        <li>To improve our website based on the information and feedback we receive</li>
        <li>To improve customer service and support</li>
        <li>To process transactions</li>
        <li>To administer a contest, promotion, survey or other site feature</li>
        <li>To send periodic emails</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Information From Third Parties</h2>
      <p>{co} will collect End User Data necessary to provide our services to our customers. End users may voluntarily provide us with information they have made available on social media websites. We may receive information from a third party that provides automated fraud detection services when you contact us. You can control how much of your information social media websites make public by changing your privacy settings.</p>

      <h2>Do We Share The Information We Collect With Third Parties?</h2>
      <p>We may share the information that we collect, both personal and non-personal, with third parties such as advertisers, contest sponsors, promotional and marketing partners, and others who provide our content or whose products or services we think may interest you. We may also share it with current and future affiliated companies and business partners, and in the event of a merger, asset sale or other business reorganization.</p>
      <p>We may engage trusted third-party service providers to perform functions such as hosting, database storage, e-mail management, credit card processing, customer service, and fulfilling orders. We may share portions of our log file data, including IP addresses, for analytics purposes. We may also disclose personal and non-personal information to government or law enforcement officials or private parties where we believe it necessary or appropriate.</p>

      <h2>How Do We Use Your Email Address?</h2>
      <p>By submitting your email address on this website, you agree to receive emails from us. You can cancel your participation at any time by clicking the unsubscribe option included in each email. We only send emails to people who have authorized us to contact them, and we do not send unsolicited commercial emails.</p>

      <h2>How Long Do We Keep Your Information?</h2>
      <p>We keep your information only so long as we need it to provide our Service to you and fulfill the purposes described in this policy. When we no longer need it and there is no legal obligation to retain it, we will remove it from our systems or depersonalize it.</p>

      <h2>How Do We Protect Your Information?</h2>
      <p>We implement a variety of security measures to maintain the safety of your personal information. All supplied sensitive information is transmitted via Secure Socket Layer (SSL) technology and encrypted into our payment gateway provider’s database. After a transaction, your private information is never kept on file. We cannot, however, ensure or warrant the absolute security of any information you transmit to us.</p>

      <h2>International Transfer</h2>
      <p>{co} is incorporated in India. Information collected may be transferred from time to time to our offices or personnel, or to third parties, located throughout the world. By using our Service, you voluntarily consent to such trans-border transfer and hosting of information, to the fullest extent allowed by applicable law.</p>

      <h2>Can I Update Or Correct My Information?</h2>
      <p>You can contact us to (1) update or correct your personally identifiable information, (2) change your communication preferences, or (3) delete the information maintained about you, by cancelling your account. We may take reasonable steps to verify your identity before granting access or making corrections. Note that it is not always technologically possible to remove every record from backups.</p>

      <h2>Governing Law</h2>
      <p>This Privacy Policy is governed by the laws of India without regard to its conflict of laws provisions. By using {co} or contacting us directly, you signify your acceptance of this Privacy Policy.</p>

      <h2>Cookies, Sessions &amp; Tracking Technologies</h2>
      <p>We use Cookies and Sessions to enhance the performance and functionality of our website. Most web browsers can be set to disable cookies; however, this may affect certain functionality. We never place Personally Identifiable Information in Cookies. We also use the Google Maps API, which may collect information in accordance with its own Privacy Policy.</p>

      <h2>Kids’ Privacy</h2>
      <p>We do not address anyone under the age of 13, and do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from anyone under 13. If you believe a child has provided us with personal data, please contact us and we will take steps to remove that information.</p>

      <h2>Changes To Our Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy to accurately reflect our Service and policies. Unless otherwise required by law, we will notify you before changes take effect. Continued use of the Service after changes means you accept the updated Privacy Policy.</p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>Don't hesitate to contact us if you have any questions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Via this link: <a href="https://www.sriyogi.site">https://www.sriyogi.site</a></li>
        <li>By email: <a href={`mailto:${site.contact.email}`}>{site.contact.email}</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
